parameters:
\n<Luerre>"...Stop with that gloomy face. The mood might rub off on
me."
\n<Ameria>"...Priest-sama. Was that treatment easy for you?"
\n<Luerre>"Angry? Why on earth should I be?"

\n<Ameria>"...Even though I study so much. Despite being a healer, I
couldn't heal the injury..."

\n<Luerre>"...Have you reflected on why you failed? Have you restudied
it?"
\n<Luerre>"I know. That's why there's no need to be angry."

\n<Ameria>"...But maybe it's impossible for me... to become a healer
like Priest-sama..."

\n<Luerre>"...Ameria. Indeed, you lack both the talent and the sense
for healing arts."

\n<Luerre>"But you possess kindness and courage to care for others.
That is the most essential power for a healer."

\n<Luerre>"I may have healed that child's injury, but it was you who
saved them... I understand that well. I'm watching."

\n<Luerre>"Don't worry. You'll become one. A much more splendid healer
than I am."

\n<Luerre>"...However. And that's exactly why. You must work harder
than anyone else and learn correctly."

\n<Luerre>"Remember this. Kindness and courage alone cannot save
people. And sometimes, that power might even cause you
pain."

\n<Luerre>"Learn the basics without rushing. Practice diligently,
don't be complacent, and take time to accumulate knowledge
and skills... And don't take books from my room without
permission."

parameters.name: 本・アルバム・ケースから出す

parameters: Luerre took a book from the bookshelf.

\n<Luerre>"The textbook you tried to take before. I'll let you read
it."

\n<Luerre>"Yes. Failure is a good lesson. You should be able to read
it now without any problems."

Luerre took out a book from her pocket and placed it on the
desk.

\n<Luerre>"What? It's just a journal. I saw it at a bookstore on the
mainland recently. I bought it because it had a nice
design."

\n<Luerre>"...From now on, when patients or injured people come, you
will examine them. Ah, of course, only when I'm by your
side. Use that journal to reflect on the day or for your
studies."

\n<Luerre>"Learn correctly, challenge yourself, and fail a lot. It's
okay. I'm here for you. I can handle a few failures."

\n<Luerre>"But just failing isn't enough. Reflect deeply. And write it
down in that book, pray. The experiences you accumulate will
eventually become a great nourishment and respond to you."
Saying that, Luerre gently placed her hand on Ameria's head.

\n<Luerre>"God and I are both watching over you. We see how hard
you're trying."

\n<Luerre>"...Also, I want to eat your cooking tonight. Make stew, the
kind with lots of chunky vegetables."

\n<Luerre>"Nuaa!? Hey, you fool, don't hug me while you're crying!
You'll dirty my clothes! Get off!"

\n<Ameria>"Priestess! I, I will do my best! I'll become a splendid
healer!"
\n<Luerre>"Ah, enough already! Let go, you fool!"
